sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073035
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inducible ampR expression combined with RhlR, LasI and eforRed expression cassettes
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct is the basis for a Quorum sensing system for two bacteria. The selection marker (amp-resistance) is induced by a RhlI(inducer)/RhlR(activator) complex. The RhlR is encoded on the construct itself, whereas the RhlI is taken up from the media. Furthermore the LasI synthetase is expressed to synthesize the autoinducer LasI for the corresponding system in another cell (BBa_K1073034). By the activation of the amp-resistance the gene of interest (in this case the chromoprotein eforRed) is expressed. Together with BBa_K1073034 the construct forms a dependency between two cells (one with BBa_K10733034, the other with BBa_K1073035).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The parts for this construct were derived from the 2013 distribution kit and the iGEM Team Uppsala.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: no considerations.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inducible ampR expression combined with LasR, RhlI and aeBlue expression cassettes
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This construct is the basis for a Quorum sensing system for two bacteria. The selection marker (amp-resistance) is induced by LasI(inducer)/LasR(activator) complex. The LasR is encoded on the construct itself, whereas the LasI is taken up from the media. Furthermore the RhlI synthetase is expressed to synthesize the autoinducer RhlI for the corresponding system in another cell (BBa_K1073035).
By the activation of the amp-resistance the gene of interest (in this case the chromoprotein aeblue) is expressed. Together with BBa_K1073035 the construct forms a dependency between two cells (one with BBa_K10733034, the other with BBa_K1073035).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The parts for this construct were derived from the 2013 distribution kit and the iGEM Team Uppsala.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: no considerations.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073028
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inducible ampicillin resistance cassette + RhlR expression cassette
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: In complex with the inducer N-butyryl-HSL, the activator RhlR binds to the Rhl promoter and enables expression. This construct provides all the parts required to express the gene behind the rhl promoter. Only the inducer N-butyryl-HSL is missing, which usually is taken up from the media. By the regulation of the inducer's concentration in the media, the expression rate of the gene of interest (in this case ampicillin beta-lactamase) can be controlled.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The biobricks for this part were taken from the 2013 distribution kit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: no considerations.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Autoinducer synthase LasI + LVA with combined eforRed chromoprotein expression cassette
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the basis for the expression of the Las auto inducer synthetase, which synthesizes LasI [N-(3-oxododecanoyl)-homoserine lactone]. LasI binds to the activator LasR. Together they activate the Las promoter. A constitutive expression of the chromoprotein eforRed is added to the construct in order to varify the expression of LasI synthetase. The construct has no promoter in front of the LasI synthetase gene. Therefore the user can choose the promoter himself (e.g. constitutive, induced, repressed, etc.)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The biobricks for this part were derived from the 2013 distribution kit and the iGEM Team Uppsala.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: no considerations.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inducible ampicillin resistance cassette + LasR expression cassette
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: In complex with the inducer PAI-1 (N-(3-oxododecanoyl)-homoserine lactone), the activator LasR binds to the Las promoter and enables expression. This construct provides all the parts required to express the gene behind the Las promoter. Only the inducer N-(3-oxododecanoyl)-homoserine lactone is missing, which usually is taken up from the media. By the regulation of the inducer's concentration in the media, the expression rate of the gene of interest (in this case ampicillin beta-lactamase) can be controlled.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The parts for this construct were taken from the 2013 distribution kit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: no considerations.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073033

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the basis for the expression of the Rhl auto inducer synthetase, which synthesizes RhlI [N-(butyryl)-homoserine lactone]. RhlI binds to the activator RhlR. Together they activate the Rhl promoter. A constitutive expression of aeblue is added to the construct in order to varify the expression of RhlI synthetase. The construct has no promoter in front of the RhlI synthetase gene. Therefore the user can choose the promoter himself (e.g. constitutive, induced, repressed, etc.)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091117
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This pLas' promoter contains the regulatory region upstream of the LasI gene in Pseudomonas aeruginosa. K091117 includes a LasR binding site as well as a -10 region modified from CATAAA to TATAAA to reflect our pLasXOR promoter design. Activation is expected to occur in the presence of the autoinducer PAI-1 and the LasR protein.
The pLas' promoter serves as a control for the evaluation of the pLasXOR promoter, part BBa_K091118.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erin Feeney
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence of the LasI upstream regulatory region is available at http://www.pubmedcentral.nih.gov/articlerender.fcgi?artid=176640
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: To minimize leaky transcription, a secondary transcriptional start site was excluded from the design.

The part begins with the RhlR binding site, and (rather arbitrarily) ends with the first transcribed base (+1).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091117
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This pLas' promoter contains the regulatory region upstream of the LasI gene in Pseudomonas aeruginosa. K091117 includes a LasR binding site as well as a -10 region modified from CATAAA to TATAAA to reflect our pLasXOR promoter design. Activation is expected to occur in the presence of the autoinducer PAI-1 and the LasR protein.
